# HTTP Headers Manipulation тАФ Bug Bounty Reference

> Scope reminder: Automated tools sirf authorized scope pe chalao (e.g. Syfe тЖТ uat-bugbounty.nonprod.syfe.com only).

---

## 1. IP Spoofing / Access Control Bypass Headers

- `X-Forwarded-For: 127.0.0.1`
  Client IP claim karta hai proxy ke peeche se

- `X-Forwarded-Host: internal.target.com`
  Original host claim karta hai

- `X-Forwarded-Proto: https`
  Protocol claim

- `X-Forwarded-Port: 8080`
  Port claim

- `X-Originating-IP: 127.0.0.1`
  Legacy IP spoof header

- `X-Remote-IP: 127.0.0.1`
  Remote IP claim

- `X-Remote-Addr: 127.0.0.1`
  Remote address claim

- `X-Client-IP: 127.0.0.1`
  Client IP claim

- `X-Real-IP: 127.0.0.1`
  Real IP claim (Nginx common)

- `X-Custom-IP-Authorization: 127.0.0.1`
  Custom IP auth check

- `True-Client-IP: 127.0.0.1`
  Akamai/Cloudflare original client IP

- `CF-Connecting-IP: 127.0.0.1`
  Cloudflare original client IP

- `Cluster-Client-IP: 127.0.0.1`
  Cluster-level client IP

- `Forwarded: for=127.0.0.1;proto=https`
  RFC 7239 standard header

**Test values:** `127.0.0.1`, `localhost`, `0.0.0.0`, `10.0.0.1`, `192.168.0.1`, target ka apna internal IP range.

